\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Gemma-3 4B: $d_{50}$ vs.\ cluster size. Coherent clusters (green) and noise clusters (gray) show indistinguishable size scaling, with Pearson $r(n, d_{50}) = 0.71$ and $0.73$ respectively. Median curves by log-spaced size bin are overlaid. The Hernandez 5--22D band is shaded; clusters enter and leave this band primarily as a function of size, not of whether they contain real relation structure.}}{7}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:d50-vs-n}{{1}{7}{Gemma-3 4B: $d_{50}$ vs.\ cluster size. Coherent clusters (green) and noise clusters (gray) show indistinguishable size scaling, with Pearson $r(n, d_{50}) = 0.71$ and $0.73$ respectively. Median curves by log-spaced size bin are overlaid. The Hernandez 5--22D band is shaded; clusters enter and leave this band primarily as a function of size, not of whether they contain real relation structure}{figure.1}{}}
